tip.text: Greasy spoon hole in the wall diner out in Norristown. Get the country scramble and you won't be disappointed. It's not a looker but it tastes amazing and really hits the spot.
The king crab was particularly memorable. Very tasty preparation. Recommended: the seafood set menu for a large banquet.

venue.name: Lei Garden Restaurant 利苑酒家

tip.text: This locals only joint is must have on a jetlagged early morning. Well worth it to trek here to get fresh egg roti and murtabak. This place is super ace.

location.address: Poh Ho Restaurant 寶和餐室
formattedAddress: Poh Ho Restaurant 寶和餐室 (7 Crane Rd. (Onan Rd.))

venue.name: Mr and Mrs Mohgan's Super Crispy Roti Prata

tip.text: Chili crab is the reason to come. Super chill vibes.
Solid prawn and pork noodles. Digging the larger sultan prawns and don't forget to get some iced coffee too.
Yowza that duck skin is good. It isn't quite like what you get in Beijing but it is about as close as I have had outside of it. The lobster and fish were particularly well done too.
If they have ridiculous truffle, get it. The chicken is the specialty and very worth it.
The beef noodle soup is the best. Don't forget pork dumplings and soup dumplings. Here's a pro tip: get the beef pancake too. They also sell dumplings frozen which are the best in the city.
Bavette steak is the best steak I've had in years.
Hawaiian meat heaven. If you get the beef don't forget to get the horseradish cream.

tip.text: Fun view and I don't care what the haters say, I like the modern structure.
Definitely get room 221. This is the view.

tip.text: Solid whiskey cocktails. Great new spot.
So fun! Get tickets in advance. Well worth the price.
E fu noodles, crab, and beef dishes are all must eat. Mustard greens also super good.
